1. copy modified files to a brand new xcode project
2. select generic ios device
3. go to product menu at the top of xcode and hit archive
4. open the directory of the xarchive file in terminal
5. using xcode make a blank plist file and paste the bottom code to it
6. name the plist file "exportOptions.plist"

<xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8">
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
  <dict>
    <key>method</key>
    <string>ad-hoc</string>
    <key>teamID</key>
    <string>YOUR_TEAM_ID</string>
    <key>uploadBitcode</key>
    <true/>
    <key>uploadSymbols</key>
    <true/>
  </dict>
</plist>

run this command
 xcodebuild -exportArchive -archivePath "file name of xarchive file"  -exportPath "anything you want as destination"  -exportOptionsPlist exportOptions.plist 

success!!!!
